---
description: Prevent migration checklist state from being updated without explicit user confirmation
alwaysApply: true
---

# Migration Checklist State Safety

- Treat migration execution state as user-owned operational metadata.
- Do not mark any migration in `prisma/migrations/000_INDEX.md` as run (`[x]`) unless the user explicitly asks to do so.
- When adding a new migration script:
  - You may add the script file.
  - You may add/update its descriptive row in the index.
  - Keep checklist state unmarked (`[ ]`) unless explicitly instructed otherwise.
- Do not infer "run" status from creating/editing a migration file.
- If uncertain whether a migration was executed, ask the user before changing checklist status.

Example:
- Allowed without extra confirmation: add `092_new_change.sql` and add its description row.
- Not allowed without explicit user request: change `- [ ] 092_new_change.sql` to `- [x] 092_new_change.sql`.
